HEADWORD: Brioche
<hw>Bri`oche"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A light sweet pastry (cake, bun or roll) made with
flour, butter, yeast, and eggs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A knitted foot cushion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

